Header.title: ECE Outreach
Header.paragraph: Students of Colorado State University bringing Electrical and Computer Engineering to students from middle school to college.

About.paragraph: ECE Outreach is devoted to making Electrical and Computer Engineering more accessible to students by delivering it in small, exciting, and informative packages. Our team works to develop exciting workshops and inspiring demonstrations, opening up the world of electronics to students who may never have considered this exciting path for their education and career.

Team.name: Brandon Crisp
Team.description: I’m a senior in Electrical Engineering, and lead of the Analog Outreach Team, and I’m interested in power electronics.

Team.name: Jameson Richard
Team.description: I'm a senior in Computer Engineering and I am interested in robotics and web development.

Team.name: Cole Taylor
Team.description: I am a senior in Electrical Engineering, the Controls team lead of the Rocket Team at CSU, and have a passion for aerospace and automotives.

Team.name: Ryan Barnes
Team.description: I am a senior in Electrical Engineering and am the current ECE Outreach Team Lead. I am interested in signal processing, specifically in the field of biomedical imaging and sensing.

Team.name: Kori Eliaz
Team.description: I’m a junior in Electrical Engineering and lead of the Media team. I’m super passionate about all things aerospace, specifically deep space communications.
